<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>September 9th, 2001.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Feign Death Fixed? Then why am I crying?</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>

From the patch message today:</p><p><ul><i>- Fixed a long-standing bug that was causing Feign Death to fail when several characters were on the NPC's hate list along with the character using Feign Death. We'd like to extend much thanks to the monk community who helped us track this one down. Also fixed a problem with the monk's 'Block' skill which inadvertantly was recapped at a lower than normal skill level in recent months. Kudos to "Faned" of the "Monkly Business" bulletin board who brow-beat Gordon with the facts until he gave in and looked at the code.</i></ul></p><p>Normally I would be leaping around the room right now in happiness, but instead I can barely see to type this through the tears. I'm sitting here watching the news, and the second tower of the World Trade Center just collapsed. The loss of life must number in the 10s of thousands, in what is without a doubt the greatest peace-time terrorist attrocity the world has ever seen. I am not an American myself, but that does not mean my heart doesnt feel the pain.</p><p>It puts it all into perspective, doesnt it, right now I couldnt care less about Feign Death.

</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
