<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>

I just received the following by email:</p><p><ul>To whom it may concern,</p><p>My name is Craig Baldwin and I am the owner of www.everquestbugs.com .  I noticed on one of your message threads someone was giving out my members URL for anyone to access a my paid service.  I ask that you close this message thread because the information contained on the members URL is copyright protected.  Handing out this URL for free violates this proctection.  I don't even mind if you just remove the link to the members area and leave the rest of the messages intact.  I just need the my members URL removed from your message thread.</p><p>The message thread that contains this information on your website is <a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=10901.topic">here</a></p><p>Thank you for your time and understanding.  Please respond to this email.</p><p>Thanks,</p><p>Craig Baldwin<br>
<a href="mailto:craigba@pathlink.com">craigba@pathlink.com</a></p></ul>
<p>Seems someone on my boards posted a link to the '<a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">members area</a>' of this so called <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">everquest bugs</a> website. People are paying $20 a time for this <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">service</a>, and yet this guy has no control whatsoever over who accesses the <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">page</a>. No kind of secure login, just an unsecure, static, <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">html page</a>.</p>
<p>However, he claims that this information about a sony product is copyrighted by him personally, so I had better be very careful and remove all <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">links</a> to the site immediately before he sends in his army of lawyers.</p>So, whatever you do, you must NOT go to <a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">this link</a> because it contains copyrighted information regarding everquest, and despite the fact that it is publicly accessable via an insecure, open access html page, you will get in trouble for violating copyright.<p><p>Oh, incase you missed it.....<a href="http://www.everquestbugs.com/321/eqmembers/sluggo/hideout.html">DONT CLICK HERE</a></p></FONT></ul>

