<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>June 13, 2001.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>By Popular Request</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p><u>The Good news:</u> I have resolved my hosting issues. I received literally hundreds of emails offering advice and hosting solutions, and I picked one which I am very happy with, which will give me all the asp and SQL support I need, at a very good price.</p><p><u>The Bad News:</u> Work is keeping me very busy at the moment, I havnt had a day off in 3 weeks, and on several occasions I have worked 30+ hour shifts. Finding time to recode the new site so I can switch to the new host has been impossible. The news system is nearly finished, but the articles system and the Equipment Database still need to be done. I dont know how long its gonna be before I can switch over, and in the mean time, the bills just keep on coming (new one arrived yesterday).</p><p>So, I have decided to take the advice of Lum the Mad, and put up a paypal donations link for a while each month. To me this is the best way of raising cash, as it is entirely optional, and I *HATE* ad-banners.</p><p>So, if you want to put in a dollar or 2 (or 10) towards keeping the site going, click on the link at the bottom of the menu on the left side. I'll keep track of the account, and once I have covered my costs for the month, I'll remove the link.</p><p>In the meantime, I am sorry about the lack of updates, but I ask you to be patient, once the new code is written and I move to the new server, news and articles will be handled by a staff of reporters, and updates should be fast and furious. Keep submitting stuff, it is all being stored up for inclusion.</p></p></FONT></ul>


<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>May 12, 2001.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Its ALIVE!</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>OK, I'm sorry, and you can stop sending the 'are you alive' emails now. I went through a bad patch at work, and the last thing you want to do after spending a nice 16 hour day coding and scripting, is go home, and do some more coding and scripting, so the site was neglected for a while, and I am sorry.</p><p>However, I am putting up this article because I have a problem. My problem is the $300 bill I have to pay for the excess bandwidth I used in the last 2 months. I can't figure it out, I stopped updating the site, and my bandwidth usage, which had been under 2gb/month, leapt up to 6gb in march, and then 8gb in April. I've already gone well over my allowance for May, and its only the 12th, I'm going to get another bill at the end of the month for that too.</p><p>So, Ive done some work on the site today, to try and reduce bandwidth. The server status will now only update once every 10 minutes, not every time you load a new page, this change was necessary to help with the problem. Also all the large files on the site (namely the excel files and the pictures in the humour section) have been moved off the server</p><p>These changes will hopefully mean a large reduction in the bandwidth I use, saving me some money, but I have another problem.</p><p>I recently learned asp and sql programming, and have some wonderful ideas for the site that you would all love. A team of reporters able to submit articles, meaning multiple news articles per day. Searchable databases of monk equipment, and more. Sounds good eh?</p><p>But wait, I said I had a problem, and the problem is this: My site is hosted on a unix box with php support, not asp, and I dont know any php.</p><p>Hopefully, with someone's help, I can solve both problems in 1 go. I need a server, a nice fast server supporting asp and sql. I'm hoping one of you monks out there is the server admin at an ISP, or something like that, and can host my site for a reduced price, or perhaps even for free?</p><p>If things keep going the way they are right now, I will not be able to afford to keep the site going for much longer. I am not going to add ad-banners, or pop-ups, or ask for donations, or make the site pay-per-view. I would rather take the site down than do something like that, I just need a nice cheap hosting solution, and I will swallow my costs so far.</p></FONT></ul>



<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>March 13, 2001.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Back!</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Well, I'm almost back to full health, so decided to catch up on some needed updates and maintenance on the site.</p><p>Before I forget, I want to thank everyone for the kind emails wishing me well. I counted them up today, and I received over 100 'get well soon' emails. I didnt reply to any of them, there were simply too many, but that certainly doesnt mean I didnt appeciate them.</p><p>Anyway. A new quest guide has been added (Bracer of Hammerfall) and Zinj's equipment spreadsheet has been updated with new items. I have a few more things to update, which will probably be done on Thursday.</p><p>I attended the monk BotB final on Test a few weeks ago, but unfortunately all the screenshots I took came out unusable (400+ of them, all so dark that you cant see a thing, dont know why the hell it happened), so I cannot do the type of article I was intending to, instead I may just put up a simple table showing who beat who in what round. If you are interested in seeing highlights of the event, castersrealm put up a video yesterday, follow the link on the links page if you want to go and download it, but its a 46mb file, so you had better have a fast connection.</p></FONT></ul>

